Description:
   Holyshield is the Priest's signature remort shield. It surrounds the
   caster in a radiant aura of holy light that retaliates specifically
   against magical attacks. Similar in structure to fireshield, it deals
   reactive holy-element damage to spell-casting attackers while absorbing
   a portion of incoming damage.

   The key difference from fireshield is that holyshield's reactive damage
   only triggers against non-physical (magical) attacks. Physical attacks
   still have their damage absorbed by the shield, but do not provoke a
   retaliatory strike.

   Shield properties:
     - Type: HOLY_SHIELD (cannot stack with other non-coexisting shields)
     - Reactive Damage: 30% of incoming damage as holy damage (spells only)
     - Absorption: 10% + (pseudo_level / 10)% of incoming damage absorbed
     - Hit Points: 5,000 + (pseudo_level * 10) -- shield breaks when depleted
     - Duration: pseudo_level / 10 rounds (halved on login)

   The reactive holy damage bypasses cloak reflection and absorption effects.
